The paper deals with algebraic complexity theory and representation theory, which are both subfields of computational complexity (cs.CC). It also involves algebraic geometry, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses orbit closures, which are related to logic and set theory (cs.LO), and the trace of a variable matrix power, which is related to control theory (cs.SY).
